  "body": "### Describe the feature\r\n\r\nScenario:\r\n\r\n- Hardhat + Foundry project\r\n- Install the npm package of a Foundry project, e.g. [`@sablier/v2-core`](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@sablier/v2-core)\r\n- Add the proper remappings in `remappings.txt`, i.e. `@sablier/v2-core/=node_modules/@sablier/v2-core/src/`\r\n- Import something from `@sablier/v2/core`, e.g. `import { LockupLinear } from \"@sablier/v2-core/types/DataTypes.sol\";`\r\n- Hope that the import works\r\n\r\nBut the import does not work:\r\n\r\n```text\r\nFailed to resolve file: \"/Users/prb/Workspace/templates/hardhat-template/node_modules/@sablier/v2-core/types/DataTypes.sol\": No such file or directory (os error 2).\r\n Check configured remappings..\r\n    --> \"/Users/prb/Workspace/templates/hardhat-template/contracts/Greeter.sol\"\r\n        \"@sablier/v2-core/types/DataTypes.sol\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt seems to me that what happens is that Hardhat disregards the remappings in `remappings.txt` when it finds a matching path in `node_modules`.\r\n\r\nThe feature request is to make remappings work with `node_modules`.\r\n\r\nFWIW, this is a blocker for our integration partners that are on Hardhat. They have to copy-paste the Sablier code for now.\r\n\r\n### Search terms\r\n\r\nfoundry,hardhat-foundry\r\n\r\n### Environment\r\n\r\n- node@18.16.0\r\n- hardhat@2.17.0",
