    "body": "We continued exploring this with @fvictorio, and we'll fix it in the next sprint (starting tomorrow).\r\n\r\nThe fix should:\r\n1. Check in the line posted above if the remapping is in `remappings.txt`, if it is, do not ignore it. — This would not work with `foundry.toml`, so there's probably better approaches to consider.\r\n2. In [hardhat core's resolver](https://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/blob/main/packages/hardhat-core/src/internal/solidity/resolver.ts#L112): don't treat replaced `importName`s as importNames, but as file paths AND source names instead.",
